OpenSSL RSA Key Generation Guide
Windows OpenSSL commands to generate RSA key pairs and export in PEM format.

Prerequisites
Verify OpenSSL installation:

text
"C:\Program Files\OpenSSL-Win64\bin\openssl.exe" version
Generate RSA Keys
1. Private Key (2048-bit)
text
"C:\Program Files\OpenSSL-Win64\bin\openssl.exe" genrsa -out private_key.pem 2048
2. Public Key from Private
text
"C:\Program Files\OpenSSL-Win64\bin\openssl.exe" rsa -in private_key.pem -pubout -out public_key.pem
View Keys
text
type private_key.pem
type public_key.pem
What is PEM Format?
PEM = Privacy Enhanced Mail (text-based format)

Used for:
Public keys
Private keys
SSL/TLS certificates

PEM Structure:
text
Header
Base64 encoded data
Footer

Private Key Example:

text
-----BEGIN RSA PRIVATE KEY-----
MIIEowIBAAKCAQEAx7J8...
...
-----END RSA PRIVATE KEY-----
Public Key Example:

text
-----BEGIN PUBLIC KEY-----
MIIBIjANBgkqhkiG9w0B...
...
-----END PUBLIC KEY-----

Quick Commands Summary
bash
# Check version
"C:\Program Files\OpenSSL-Win64\bin\openssl.exe" version

# Generate private key
"C:\Program Files\OpenSSL-Win64\bin\openssl.exe" genrsa -out private_key.pem 2048

# Extract public key
"C:\Program Files\OpenSSL-Win64\bin\openssl.exe" rsa -in private_key.pem -pubout -out public_key.pem

# View files
type private_key.pem
type public_key.pem
Files Created
private_key.pem - Keep secret!

public_key.pem - Safe to share
